02/08/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Interior Minister Ivica Dacic confirmed on Saturday (July 31st) that his family has been placed under police protection because of threats coming from organised crime groups. Local media reports that one of the most dangerous mafia bosses in Serbia told Dacic they would kidnap one of his children unless the police halt actions against him. The union of police officers vowed to continue its fight against organised crime. (B92, Tanjug - 31/07/10)
